JOHANNESBURG - Transport minister Dipuo Peters announced an interim Prasa board.The minister has been briefing the media on developments at Prasa.Prasa s interim board will be chaired by Nazir Alli, former chief executive of the South African National Roads Agency (Sanral), who retired in September.Former Transport spokesperson, Tiyani Rikhotso, and former general-secretary of the National Union of Minerworkers (NUM) have also been seconded to the interim board.The other additional members to make up the eight-member board are Xolile George from South African Local Government Association (Salga), Constance Maleho from the Department of Transport, Natalie Skeepers, Ronny Mkhwanazi, and a National Treasury representative.Peters said she's well within her rights to dissolve the Prasa board.Former board chairperson Popo Molefe is heading to court to challenge the decision.I welcome the interim PRASA Board. Solid and experienced individuals. Previous Board forgot the mandate of PRASA but focused on side issues.- Additional reporting ANA eNCA